str2: Therefore, then. Apparently a primary word; certainly, or accordingly.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
(a) pay, wages, salary, (b) reward, recompense, punishment. Apparently a primary word; pay for service, good or bad.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Injustice, unrighteousness, hurt. From adikos; injustice; morally, wrongfulness.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I acquire, win, get, purchase, buy, (b) I possess, win mastery over. A primary verb; to get, i.e. Acquire.
A place, piece of land, field, property, estate. Diminutive of chora; a spot or plot of ground.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Middle - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
Falling headlong, prone. From pro; leaning forward, i.e. Head foremost.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A strengthened form of a primary verb, which only occurs in this and another prolonged form as alternate in certain tenses; to crack open.
Middle, in the middle, between, in the midst of. From meta; middle (neuter) noun).
All, the whole, every kind of. Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Probably strengthened from splen; an intestine; figuratively, pity or sympathy.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: Or ekchuno ek-khoo'-no from ek and cheo; to pour forth; figuratively, to bestow.
